cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.CR 

This paper focuses on person re-identification, which is a computer vision task related to image analysis and recognition. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a deep learning model for learning image representations, which suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of unsupervised learning, which could place it in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also evaluates its approach on benchmark datasets, which could suggest it belongs to cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper addresses the issue of cross-dataset re-ID, which could place it in cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
